\",\n","        \"QUEENSWAY\",\n","        \"LUNG WO ROAD\",\n","        \"COTTON TREE DRIVE\",\n","        \"GLENEALY\",\n","        \"UPPER ALBERT ROAD\",\n","        \"QUEEN'S ROAD CENTRAL\",\n","    ]\n","    pattern = \"|\".join(central_keywords)\n","\n","    # Subset: roads whose RoadName contains any of these keywords\n","    if \"RoadName\" not in df_all.columns:\n","        raise ValueError(\"CSV must contain a 'RoadName' column.\")\n","    df_central = df_all[df_all[\"RoadName\"].str.contains(pattern, case=False, na=False)].copy()\n","\n","    # Standardised road name\n","    df_central[\"RoadName_std\"] = (\n","        df_central[\"RoadName\"]\n","        .fillna(\"\")\n","        .str.strip()\n","        .str.upper()\n","    )\n","\n","    # Ensure link_key exists; if not, create from RoadName_std + StationNo\n","    if \"link_key\" not in df_central.columns:\n","        if \"StationNo\" not in df_central.columns:\n","            raise ValueError(\"CSV must contain 'link_key' or 'StationNo' to create a link identifier.\")\n","        df_central[\"link_key\"] = (\n","            df_central[\"RoadName_std\"].astype(str)\n","            + \"|\" +\n","            df_central[\"StationNo\"].astype(str)\n","        )\n","\n","    # Year & CurAADT basic cleaning\n","    if \"year\" not in df_central.columns:\n","        raise ValueError(\"CSV must contain a 'year' column.\")\n","    if \"CurAADT\" not in df_central.columns:\n","        raise ValueError(\"CSV must contain a 'CurAADT' column (current AADT).\")\n","\n","    df_central[\"year\"] = pd.to_numeric(df_central[\"year\"], errors=\"coerce\").astype(\"Int64\")\n","    df_central[\"CurAADT\"] = pd.to_numeric(df_central[\"CurAADT\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n","\n","    # Keep only valid rows\n","    df_central = df_central.dropna(subset=[\"year\", \"CurAADT\"])\n","    df_central[\"year\"] = df_central[\"year\"].astype(int)\n","\n","    # Focus on 2010–2027 (you can adjust)\n","    df_central = df_central[df_central[\"year\"].between(2010, 2027, inclusive=\"both\")]\n","\n","    return df_central\n","\n","\n","df_central = load_central_data()\n","\n","if df_central.empty:\n","    st.error(\"No Central corridor data found. Please check hk_aadt_all_years.csv.\")\n","    st.stop()\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 2. Helper functions for models & metrics\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","def linear_model_fit_predict(\n","    sub_df: pd.DataFrame,\n","    train_start: int,\n","    train_end: int,\n","    predict_years: list[int]\n","):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Fit a simple linear regression on (year, CurAADT) and predict for predict_years.\n","    Returns a dict: {year: prediction}\n","    \"\"\"\n","    mask_train = (sub_df[\"year\"] >= train_start) & (sub_df[\"year\"] <= train_end)\n","    df_train = sub_df[mask_train].copy().sort_values(\"year\")\n","\n","    if df_train[\"year\"].nunique() < 2:\n","        return {}\n","\n","    X_train = df_train[\"year\"].values.reshape(-1, 1)\n","    y_train = df_train[\"CurAADT\"].values\n","\n","    model = LinearRegression()\n","    model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n","\n","    preds = {}\n","    if predict_years:\n","        X_pred = np.array(sorted(predict_years)).reshape(-1, 1)\n","        y_pred = model.predict(X_pred)\n","        for y, v in zip(X_pred.flatten(), y_pred):\n","            preds[int(y)] = float(v)\n","\n","    return preds\n","\n","\n","def naive_last_year_predict(sub_df: pd.DataFrame, predict_years: list[int]):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Naive baseline: use the last available actual CurAADT for all future years.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if sub_df.empty:\n","        return {}\n","    last_row = sub_df.sort_values(\"year\").iloc[-1]\n","    last_value = float(last_row[\"CurAADT\"])\n","    return {int(y): last_value for y in predict_years}\n","\n","\n","def moving_average_predict(sub_df: pd.DataFrame, window: int, predict_years: list[int]):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Moving average baseline: use the mean of the last 'window' actual years for all future years.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    df_sorted = sub_df.sort_values(\"year\")\n","    if len(df_sorted) < window:\n","        return {}\n","    last_vals = df_sorted[\"CurAADT\"].tail(window)\n","    mean_val = float(last_vals.mean())\n","    return {int(y): mean_val for y in predict_years}\n","\n","\n","def apply_scenario(pred_dict: dict[int, float], scenario: str):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Apply scenario multiplier to predictions.\n","    scenario: \"Normal\", \"High growth\", \"Low growth\"\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if scenario == \"High growth\":\n","        factor = 1.15  # +15%\n","    elif scenario == \"Low growth\":\n","        factor = 0.85  # -15%\n","    else:\n","        factor = 1.0\n","\n","    return {y: v * factor for y, v in pred_dict.items()}\n","\n","\n","def compute_global_metrics(df: pd.DataFrame, latest_year: int | None = None):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Compute some high-level metrics for the dashboard header.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    if latest_year is None:\n","        latest_year = df[\"year\"].max()\n","\n","    df_latest = df[df[\"year\"] == latest_year]\n","    total_latest = df_latest[\"CurAADT\"].sum() if not df_latest.empty else np.nan\n","\n","    # Simple 5-year growth (if data available)\n","    if latest_year - 5 in df[\"year\"].unique():\n","        df_base = df[df[\"year\"] == latest_year - 5]\n","        total_base = df_base[\"CurAADT\"].sum()\n","        if total_base and total_base != 0:\n","            growth_5y = (total_latest - total_base) / total_base * 100.0\n","        else:\n","            growth_5y = np.nan\n","    else:\n","        growth_5y = np.nan\n","\n","    # Top link by latest AADT\n","    top_link = None\n","    if not df_latest.empty:\n","        row = df_latest.sort_values(\"CurAADT\", ascending=False).iloc[0]\n","        top_link = (row[\"RoadName\"], row[\"CurAADT\"], row[\"link_key\"])\n","\n","    return {\n","        \"latest_year\": latest_year,\n","        \"total_latest\": total_latest,\n","        \"growth_5y\": growth_5y,\n","        \"top_link\": top_link,\n","    }\n","\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 3. Sidebar controls\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","st.title(\"Hong Kong Central Corridor AADT Dashboard\")\n","\n","sidebar = st.sidebar\n","sidebar.header(\"Controls\")\n","\n","years_all = sorted(df_central[\"year\"].unique().tolist())\n","min_year, max_year = min(years_all), max(years_all)\n","\n","# Year range for exploration\n","year_range = sidebar.slider(\n","    \"Year range for analysis\",\n","    min_value=min_year,\n","    max_value=max_year,\n","    value=(max(min_year, max_year - 7), max_year),\n","    step=1,\n",")\n","\n","# Training period for models\n","train_start, train_end = sidebar.slider(\n","    \"Training period (for models)\",\n","    min_value=min_year,\n","    max_value=max_year,\n","    value=(max(min_year, max_year - 7), max_year - 2 if max_year - 2 > min_year else max_year - 1),\n","    step=1,\n","    help=\"Years used to fit the linear model.\"\n",")\n","\n","# Forecast years (beyond train_end)\n","future_candidates = [y for y in years_all if y > train_end] + [max_year + 1, max_year + 2, max_year + 3]\n","future_candidates = sorted(set(future_candidates))\n","future_years = sidebar.multiselect(\n","    \"Future years to forecast\",\n","    options=future_candidates,\n","    default=[y for y in future_candidates if y <= max_year + 2],\n",")\n","\n","# Scenario selection\n","scenario = sidebar.selectbox(\n","    \"Scenario for forecasts\",\n","    options=[\"Normal\", \"High growth\", \"Low growth\"],\n","    help=\"Scales the forecast up or down to mimic different growth scenarios.\"\n",")\n","\n","# Normalization toggle\n","normalize = sidebar.checkbox(\n","    \"Normalize AADT to index (base year = 100)\",\n","    value=False,\n","    help=\"Helps compare relative changes across different road links.\"\n",")\n","\n","# Link selection (primary + comparison)\n","link_df = (\n","    df_central[[\"link_key\", \"RoadName\"]]\n","    .drop_duplicates(subset=\"link_key\")\n","    .sort_values(\"RoadName\")\n",")\n","\n","link_labels = [\n","    f\"{row['RoadName']} ({row['link_key']})\"\n","    for _, row in link_df.iterrows()\n","]\n","label_to_key = {\n","    f\"{row['RoadName']} ({row['link_key']})\": row[\"link_key\"]\n","    for _, row in link_df.iterrows()\n","}\n","\n","primary_label = sidebar.selectbox(\"Primary road link\", link_labels)\n","primary_key = label_to_key[primary_label]\n","\n","compare_labels = sidebar.multiselect(\n","    \"Additional links for comparison (up to 3)\",\n","    options=[l for l in link_labels if l != primary_label],\n","    default=[],\n","    max_selections=3,\n",")\n","\n","compare_keys = [label_to_key[l] for l in compare_labels]\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 4. Header metrics\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","metrics = compute_global_metrics(df_central)\n","col1, col2, col3 = st.columns(3)\n","\n","latest_year = metrics[\"latest_year\"]\n","col1.metric(\n","    f\"Total AADT in Central Corridor ({latest_year})\",\n","    f\"{metrics['total_latest']:,.0f}\" if not np.isnan(metrics[\"total_latest\"]) else \"N/A\",\n",")\n","\n","if not np.isnan(metrics[\"growth_5y\"]):\n","    col2.metric(\n","        \"5-year growth in total AADT\",\n","        f\"{metrics['growth_5y']:.1f} %\",\n","    )\n","else:\n","    col2.metric(\n","        \"5-year growth in total AADT\",\n","        \"N/A\",\n","    )\n","\n","if metrics[\"top_link\"] is not None:\n","    name, val, key_ = metrics[\"top_link\"]\n","    col3.metric(\n","        \"Highest AADT link (latest year)\",\n","        f\"{name}\",\n","        help=f\"{name} ({key_}) – {val:,.0f} vehicles/day\"\n","    )\n","else:\n","    col3.metric(\"Highest AADT link (latest year)\", \"N/A\")\n","\n","st.markdown(\"---\")\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 5. Tabs\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","tab_explore, tab_models, tab_rankings, tab_about, tab_faq = st.tabs(\n","    [\"Exploration\", \"Model comparison\", \"Rankings\", \"About / Methodology\", \"FAQ\"]\n",")\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 6. Exploration tab\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","with tab_explore:\n","    st.subheader(\"Traffic trends for selected road links\")\n","\n","    # Filter by year_range\n","    df_range = df_central[\n","        (df_central[\"year\"] >= year_range[0]) &\n","        (df_central[\"year\"] <= year_range[1])\n","    ].copy()\n","\n","    if df_range.empty:\n","        st.info(\"No data in the chosen year range.\")\n","    else:\n","        # Prepare a list of selected keys: primary + comparison\n","        selected_keys = [primary_key] + compare_keys\n","\n","        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n","\n","        for key in selected_keys:\n","            sub = df_range[df_range[\"link_key\"] == key].sort_values(\"year\")\n","            if sub.empty:\n","                continue\n","            series = sub[[\"year\", \"CurAADT\"]].dropna()\n","\n","            if normalize:\n","                base_year = series[\"year\"].min()\n","                base_val = series.loc[series[\"year\"] == base_year, \"CurAADT\"].iloc[0]\n","                if base_val != 0:\n","                    series = series.copy()\n","                    series[\"CurAADT_norm\"] = series[\"CurAADT\"] / base_val * 100.0\n","                    y_vals = series[\"CurAADT_norm\"]\n","                    label_suffix = f\" (index, base={base_year})\"\n","                else:\n","                    y_vals = series[\"CurAADT\"]\n","                    label_suffix = \"\"\n","            else:\n","                y_vals = series[\"CurAADT\"]\n","                label_suffix = \"\"\n","\n","            road_name = sub[\"RoadName\"].iloc[0]\n","            ax.plot(\n","                series[\"year\"],\n","                y_vals,\n","                marker=\"o\",\n","                label=f\"{road_name} ({key}){label_suffix}\",\n","            )\n","\n","        ax.set_xlabel(\"Year\")\n","        ax.set_ylabel(\"AADT (index=100)\" if normalize else \"CurAADT\")\n","        ax.set_title(\"AADT trends within the selected year range\")\n","        ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","        ax.legend(fontsize=8)\n","        plt.tight_layout()\n","        st.pyplot(fig)\n","\n","        st.write(\"Data for selected links in the chosen year range:\")\n","        st.dataframe(\n","            df_range[df_range[\"link_key\"].isin(selected_keys)][\n","                [\"year\", \"RoadName\", \"link_key\", \"CurAADT\"]\n","            ].sort_values([\"RoadName\", \"year\"])\n","        )\n","\n","        # Optional map view if coordinates exist\n","        if {\"Latitude\", \"Longitude\"}.issubset(df_central.columns):\n","            st.subheader(\"Map of monitoring locations (Central corridor)\")\n","            df_map = df_central.dropna(subset=[\"Latitude\", \"Longitude\"]).copy()\n","            df_map[\"lat\"] = pd.to_numeric(df_map[\"Latitude\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n","            df_map[\"lon\"] = pd.to_numeric(df_map[\"Longitude\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n","            df_map = df_map.dropna(subset=[\"lat\", \"lon\"])\n","\n","            if not df_map.empty:\n","                st.map(df_map[[\"lat\", \"lon\"]], zoom=12)\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 7. Model comparison tab\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","with tab_models:\n","    st.subheader(\"Model comparison for the primary link\")\n","\n","    sub_full = df_central[df_central[\"link_key\"] == primary_key].sort_values(\"year\")\n","    if sub_full.empty:\n","        st.info(\"No data for the selected primary link.\")\n","    else:\n","        road_name = sub_full[\"RoadName\"].iloc[0]\n","\n","        # Years used for training / evaluation\n","        train_mask = (sub_full[\"year\"] >= train_start) & (sub_full[\"year\"] <= train_end)\n","        df_train = sub_full[train_mask]\n","        df_eval = sub_full[sub_full[\"year\"] > train_end]\n","\n","        # Determine prediction years: evaluation years + future_years (unique)\n","        pred_years = sorted(set(df_eval[\"year\"].tolist() + future_years))\n","\n","        # Linear model\n","        lin_preds = linear_model_fit_predict(sub_full, train_start, train_end, pred_years)\n","        lin_preds = apply_scenario(lin_preds, scenario)\n","\n","        # Naive last-year model\n","        naive_preds = naive_last_year_predict(sub_full, pred_years)\n","        naive_preds = apply_scenario(naive_preds, scenario)\n","\n","        # Moving average model (window=3)\n","        ma_preds = moving_average_predict(sub_full, window=3, predict_years=pred_years)\n","        ma_preds = apply_scenario(ma_preds, scenario)\n","\n","        # Plot actual + predictions\n","        fig2, ax2 = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n","\n","        # Actual series (full range)\n","        ax2.plot(\n","            sub_full[\"year\"],\n","            sub_full[\"CurAADT\"],\n","            marker=\"o\",\n","            color=\"tab:blue\",\n","            label=\"Actual CurAADT\",\n","        )\n","\n","        # Draw vertical line at train_end\n","        ax2.axvline(\n","            x=train_end + 0.1,\n","            color=\"gray\",\n","            linestyle=\"--\",\n","            linewidth=1,\n","            label=\"End of training period\",\n","        )\n","\n","        def plot_pred_series(pred_dict, label, color, style):\n","            if not pred_dict:\n","                return\n","            years_ = sorted(pred_dict.keys())\n","            vals_ = [pred_dict[y] for y in years_]\n","            ax2.plot(\n","                years_,\n","                vals_,\n","                marker=\"o\",\n","                linestyle=style,\n","                color=color,\n","                label=label,\n","            )\n","\n","        plot_pred_series(lin_preds, f\"Linear model ({scenario})\", \"red\", \"--\")\n","        plot_pred_series(naive_preds, f\"Naive last-year ({scenario})\", \"orange\", \":\")\n","        plot_pred_series(ma_preds, f\"Moving average (3-year, {scenario})\", \"green\", \"-.\")\n","\n","        ax2.set_title(f\"{road_name} ({primary_key}) – model comparison\")\n","        ax2.set_xlabel(\"Year\")\n","        ax2.set_ylabel(\"CurAADT\")\n","        ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","        ax2.legend(fontsize=8)\n","        plt.tight_layout()\n","        st.pyplot(fig2)\n","\n","        # Error table for years where we have actual values after train_end\n","        rows_err = []\n","        for _, row in sub_full.iterrows():\n","            y = int(row[\"year\"])\n","            if y <= train_end:\n","                continue\n","            actual = float(row[\"CurAADT\"])\n","\n","            def err(pred_dict):\n","                if y not in pred_dict:\n","                    return np.nan, np.nan\n","                pred = pred_dict[y]\n","                abs_e = abs(pred - actual)\n","                pct_e = abs_e / actual * 100.0 if actual != 0 else np.nan\n","                return abs_e, pct_e\n","\n","            lin_abs, lin_pct = err(lin_preds)\n","            naive_abs, naive_pct = err(naive_preds)\n","            ma_abs, ma_pct = err(ma_preds)\n","\n","            rows_err.append(\n","                {\n","                    \"year\": y,\n","                    \"Actual\": actual,\n","                    \"Linear_pred\": lin_preds.get(y, np.nan),\n","                    \"Naive_pred\": naive_preds.get(y, np.nan),\n","                    \"MovingAvg_pred\": ma_preds.get(y, np.nan),\n","                    \"Linear_abs_err\": lin_abs,\n","                    \"Linear_pct_err\": lin_pct,\n","                    \"Naive_abs_err\": naive_abs,\n","                    \"Naive_pct_err\": naive_pct,\n","                    \"MovingAvg_abs_err\": ma_abs,\n","                    \"MovingAvg_pct_err\": ma_pct,\n","                }\n","            )\n","\n","        if rows_err:\n","            st.subheader(\"Error metrics (for years with actual data after training period)\")\n","            df_err = pd.DataFrame(rows_err).sort_values(\"year\")\n","            st.dataframe(df_err)\n","\n","        # Short textual explanation\n","        st.markdown(\n","            f\"\"\"\n","**Notes on the models**\n","\n","- **Linear model**: fits a straight line to the training years {train_start}–{train_end},\n","  then extrapolates into the future.\n","- **Naive last-year model**: uses the last observed AADT as a flat forecast.\n","- **Moving average model**: uses the mean of the last 3 available years as a flat forecast.\n","- **Scenario: {scenario}** – forecast values are scaled to mimic higher or lower growth rates.\n","            \"\"\"\n","        )\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 8. Rankings tab\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","with tab_rankings:\n","    st.subheader(\"Rankings and summary tables\")\n","\n","    # Choose year for ranking\n","    rank_year = st.selectbox(\n","        \"Select year for rankings\",\n","        options=sorted(df_central[\"year\"].unique().tolist()),\n","        index=max(0, len(sorted(df_central[\"year\"].unique())) - 1),\n","    )\n","\n","    df_rank = df_central[df_central[\"year\"] == rank_year].copy()\n","    if df_rank.empty:\n","        st.info(\"No data for this year.\")\n","    else:\n","        # Top 10 by AADT\n","        st.markdown(f\"### Top 10 links by CurAADT ({rank_year})\")\n","        df_top10 = (\n","            df_rank.sort_values(\"CurAADT\", ascending=False)\n","            [[\"RoadName\", \"link_key\", \"CurAADT\"]]\n","            .head(10)\n","            .reset_index(drop=True)\n","        )\n","        st.dataframe(df_top10)\n","\n","        # Growth over chosen period (if available)\n","        st.markdown(\"### Links with strongest growth (in chosen analysis range)\")\n","        # Compute growth between first and last year in year_range\n","        year_start, year_end = year_range\n","        df_start = df_central[df_central[\"year\"] == year_start][[\"link_key\", \"CurAADT\"]]\n","        df_end = df_central[df_central[\"year\"] == year_end][[\"link_key\", \"CurAADT\"]]\n","\n","        df_growth = (\n","            df_start.merge(df_end, on=\"link_key\", how=\"inner\", suffixes=(\"_start\", \"_end\"))\n","        )\n","        df_growth[\"growth_abs\"] = df_growth[\"CurAADT_end\"] - df_growth[\"CurAADT_start\"]\n","        df_growth[\"growth_pct\"] = np.where(\n","            df_growth[\"CurAADT_start\"] != 0,\n","            df_growth[\"growth_abs\"] / df_growth[\"CurAADT_start\"] * 100.0,\n","            np.nan,\n","        )\n","\n","        df_growth = df_growth.merge(\n","            link_df[[\"link_key\", \"RoadName\"]],\n","            on=\"link_key\",\n","            how=\"left\",\n","        )\n","\n","        df_growth_top = (\n","            df_growth.sort_values(\"growth_pct\", ascending=False)\n","            [[\"RoadName\", \"link_key\", \"CurAADT_start\", \"CurAADT_end\", \"growth_abs\", \"growth_pct\"]]\n","            .head(10)\n","            .reset_index(drop=True)\n","        )\n","        st.dataframe(df_growth_top)\n","\n","        st.markdown(\n","            f\"\"\"\n","The growth table compares AADT between **{year_start}** and **{year_end}**\n","for links that have data in both years.\n","            \"\"\"\n","        )\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 9. About / Methodology tab\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","with tab_about:\n","    st.subheader(\"About this dashboard\")\n","\n","    st.markdown(\n","        \"\"\"\n","This dashboard presents **Annual Average Daily Traffic (AADT)** estimates for\n","road links in Hong Kong's **Central corridor**, based on the Hong Kong Transport\n","Department's **Annual Traffic Census** data.\n","\n","### Data\n","\n","- **Source**: Hong Kong Transport Department – Annual Traffic Census (multiple years).\n","- **Spatial focus**: Central corridor, identified using road name keywords such as\n","  *Harcourt Road, Connaught Road, Garden Road, Queensway,* and related streets.\n","- **Key variables**:\n","  - `year`: census year.\n","  - `CurAADT`: estimated annual average daily traffic for each link.\n","  - `RoadName`, `StationNo`, `link_key`: identifiers for road links or counting stations.\n","\n","### Data processing\n","\n","1. Load the combined AADT file `hk_aadt_all_years.csv`.\n","2. Filter rows whose road names contain specific **Central corridor keywords**.\n","3. Construct a stable link identifier `link_key` from road name and station number\n","   (if not already present).\n","4. Clean and type‑cast:\n","   - Convert `year` to integer.\n","   - Convert `CurAADT` to numeric and drop rows with missing values.\n","5. Restrict the analysis to a reasonable time window (e.g. 2010–2027).\n","\n","### Modelling\n","\n","The app implements three simple forecasting approaches at the **link level**:\n","\n","1. **Linear regression model**\n","   - Fits a straight line between `year` and `CurAADT` over a user‑selected\n","     training period.\n","   - Extrapolates into evaluation and future years.\n","2. **Naive last‑year model**\n","   - Uses the last observed AADT as a flat forecast for all subsequent years.\n","3. **Moving average model (3‑year)**\n","   - Uses the mean of the last three available years as a flat forecast.\n","\n","These models are intended as **didactic examples**, not production‑grade traffic forecasts.\n","\n","### Scenarios\n","\n","To illustrate uncertainty and alternative futures, forecasts can be scaled with\n","simple scenarios:\n","\n","- **Normal**: no adjustment.\n","- **High growth**: forecast values multiplied by 1.15 (approx. +15%).\n","- **Low growth**: forecast values multiplied by 0.85 (approx. −15%).\n","\n","These scenario factors are arbitrary and chosen only for demonstration.\n","\n","### Limitations\n","\n","- The models do **not** explicitly account for:\n","  - Economic shocks or pandemics.\n","  - Major infrastructure changes or road works.\n","  - Land‑use changes or modal shift to public transport.\n","- Data issues such as missing years, station relocations, or re‑definitions\n","  of road segments can affect comparability over time.\n","\n","Despite these limitations, the dashboard shows how open data and simple models\n","can be combined to support **exploratory traffic analysis** and\n","**communication with non‑technical audiences**.\n","        \"\"\"\n","    )\n","\n","# =========================================================\n","# 10. FAQ tab\n","# =========================================================\n","\n","with tab_faq:\n","    st.subheader(\"Frequently Asked Questions\")\n","\n","    st.markdown(\n","        \"\"\"\n","**1. What does AADT mean?**\n","AADT stands for *Annual Average Daily Traffic*. It is an estimate of the\n","average number of vehicles passing a specific road link per day over an\n","entire year.\n","\n","---\n","\n","**2. Why do some links have missing years?**\n","Not every counting station is measured or published in every year. In some\n","cases, stations may be relocated, renamed, or replaced, which can lead to\n","gaps in the time series.\n","\n","---\n","\n","**3. Why are there different models?**\n","Each model captures a different idea of how traffic evolves:\n","\n","- The **linear model** assumes a roughly linear trend over time.\n","- The **naive last‑year model** assumes that the most recent conditions will\n","  persist unchanged.\n","- The **moving average model** smooths short‑term fluctuations and emphasises\n","  medium‑term levels.\n","\n","Comparing them helps users understand how sensitive forecasts are to basic\n","assumptions.\n","\n","---\n","\n","**4. How should I interpret the scenario options?**\n","Scenarios (**Normal**, **High growth**, **Low growth**) are not formal\n","forecasting scenarios. They simply scale the model outputs to illustrate how\n","AADT might look under faster or slower growth. They are useful for\n","**what‑if** style exploration, not as official predictions.\n","\n","---\n","\n","**5. Can I use these numbers for engineering design or policy decisions?**\n","No. This dashboard is a **student project / demonstration tool**. While it\n","uses real data, the modelling choices are simplified. Any serious engineering\n","or policy analysis should rely on more detailed models and official forecasts.\n","\n","---\n","\n","**6. How was the Central corridor defined?**\n","The Central corridor in this dashboard is identified via a set of\n","road‑name keywords (for example *Harcourt Road, Connaught Road, Garden Road,*\n","and related streets). This is a pragmatic definition for analysis rather than\n","an official boundary.\n","\n","---\n","\n","**7. Can I download the data shown here?**\n","The underlying data come from publicly available Annual Traffic Census\n","datasets. You can also export the filtered tables directly from this app\n","(using the *Download as CSV* button in Streamlit, if enabled in your\n","environment) or by re‑running the data processing steps in a Jupyter or\n","Colab notebook.\n","        \"\"\"\n","    )"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"mg50rairhkEG","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776933250779,"user_tz":-480,"elapsed":105,"user":{"displayName":"Man tik Chan","userId":"08816915228278197018"}},"outputId":"df87db6c-0d25-41b1-eb4c-fa14076e0be7"},"exec